Is the glass half-empty or half-full?
Who cares about some retarded glass when my life sucks the way it does....

Well another day went by. The last day of precamp. Subway. Planned on going to a show that fell though. Full day of computer because I have no effing life I need to find something to do a lot. My mom grounded me from the mall.
I wrote another peom ask me if you want to see it.

Well to day was so mother effing awesome. I saw Seether live. I saw Three Days Grace live. I saw Breaking Benjamin live.(yes they all needed their own sentence.)Oh and there was that one band ohh whats it called.......Oh thats right Evanescence. Seether was still my favorite though they effing covered Nirvana. Evanesence covered Korn. Three Days Grace was just awesome. I do believe I confused people with how I rocked out. Thats right PlungerBoy rocked out. I got 2 sweat wristbands, one of which Melissa has but it's cool.


     Oh and I have band news no not Philo band. My new "Life Metal" band is jamming sunday after church. We are still nameless. Oh and I haven't given up on younolongerexist either. I still want Dayne. We need some one who can sing.

     In other news you know all of these things are incrediblly great but you know what being the little pessimist that i am I still find things to be sad about. It's what I do. I won't bore anyone with details.

PlungerBoy.

Wow an actual update.

Well sad days continue but some good things poke there head out every once and a while. I get to go see Seether, Three Days Grace, Breaking Benjamin, and Evanescence. I am excited. Sad but excited.

Zach and I finally figured out a band name. younolongerexist.
I have to remake everything I did because I misspelled it I did do it at like 3 in the morning.

Well because I don't want to type petty simple day things I am done.


Chase, sad bassist of the band younolongerexist, who gets to see his favorite band live.

No lately I have been thinking about, what I have ben thinking about lately. Me personlly, I am a very enlightened) person in fact I may be most on of the most enlightened people in my grade (not intelligent enlightened). Now my family and other people praise me for this and I don't really want it I am grateful for it but I don't want it. Being the way I am knowing the things I know is not something good I am just going on 15 dammit, and I worry about not finding a perosn to love the rest of my life. THat seems quite like a mid-life crisis. Am I gonna die at like 28? Another very concerning thing. NOw everyone knows I changed my life and everything. I went from breaking into a persons house to Being a very religous person like in two months. I did it for all the wrong reasons. I very much do not regret it, it was the best thing that I have ever done in my life. Noe of it was for me. Now this is something I feel obliged to tell everyone. JUST BECAUSE YOU HAVE FOUND JESUS DOES NOT MEAN LIFE IS EASY. In fact life gets a lot harder but just know that you walk with God makes the bad times all right. Another thing. IF ONE MORE PERSON TELLS ME TO STOP BEING SOMEONES FRIEND  BECAUSE THEY ARE A BAD PERSON I WILL SMACK YOU HARD!!!!! Someone not being a good person is so mch more of a reason to be there friend. Why because you are a good person they are a bad person, help them forgive them Jesus forgave you. You can forgive people. If you quit being a persons friend just because they did something bad you in turn are a worse person. I am done with rant now for how may past few days have been.

Whoose name is Jeff but His nick name is Heffa. But any wasy while we were there My grandma called George's house and left an angry message because no one answered the phone. Then me an George played some Open Up of My Heart. Then I came home around 10:36 and now here I am. Wow this journal entry was like Tyler McKean size, but I am done now.

I know to much for my own good.
so confused. my world is gone.

Well I am still confused about a lot of things but i am trying to be as optimistic as possible. I am doing better I am happier. I have found the best way to do that is sourrond my self as much as my friends as possible. I have also found that I feel home anywhere but my house. Our phone is broke, and I only have comunication though MSN and my Mother is hogging the computer today even I after mowed the inch high grass. Things are beginning to look up. but i have to block out my very pessimistic point of veiw just about every positive thing i find in my life my brain comes back with something 3 times more negitive. That musical is great, and very complicated and there are some very talented people in Philo and I am very glad to work with them and know them. I am done.
